items.name: OTT, Inc.
items.description:

items.name: STERLING LEDET & ASSOCIATES INC
items.description:
Ledet Training operates and maintains instructor-led software training centers with multiple dedicated computer labs in Atlanta, Chicago, Denver, Houston, San Diego and Washington DC.  We also deliver virtual instructor-led training events in online classrooms and private instructor-led training events onsite at client locations.

Our training centers are full-time, long-term conventional commercial office leases. We are headquartered in Atlanta Georgia where we own a 10,200 sf corporate headquarters building and training center.

We are authorized training partners for Adobe, Autodesk, Microsoft, Filemaker, Unity Technologies and several smaller software vendors.

We serve a large variety of corporate and organizational clients across a broad swath of industries. Much of our clientele is government, military and academic in addition to public and private businesses. The majority of our class participants are employed professionals whose employer is investing in and sponsoring professional skills development and continuing education for their staff.

Ledet Training was founded in 1996. For two decades, we've been one of Adobe's largest authorized training centers, as well as being Autodesk, and Microsoft authorized. We've operated software training centers inside the commercial facilities of Apple Computer, QuarkXPress, and Fuji Film.

items.name: TechHouse
items.description:
The Cloud:
We have been helping business move to the Microsoft Cloud since it was first released.
 
Since then, we have set up online email, SharePoint, Skype for Business and CRM. Our team of certified professionals has designed cloud applications serving thousands of users. One of our team members has even helped "write the book" on the cloud

Technology Experts:
Since 1995, TechHouse's Special Forces team of Microsoft System Experts has architected, developed, implemented and supported IT solutions based on Microsoft technologies. 
 
It is not easy to join our Special Forces team.  Each member has over 10 years of experience with their specialty.  And it is not enough to be super smart. Each Special Forces member is personable and committed to our mutual success.  To be a member of our Special Forces team is to live our 4 core values: Integrity, Caring, Creativity and Excellence.
 
Our team focuses on solutions comprised of one or more of the following tools: SQL Server, .NET, Visual Studio, econnect, C#, Web Services, Dynamics GP, Mobility, Office 365, Power BI, CRM , Windows Server, Lync/Skype4B, Project/Project Online, MS Office, SharePoint/SharePoint Online, or Exchange/Exchange Online.
 

List of Offerings: 
Cloud: Sample implementation and support solutions include Office 365, Email, SharePoint, Lync and CRM in the Cloud, Custom Cloud Applications, and Migrating existing Business Software to the Cloud.
Systems Integration: Various ERP and database systems with Reporting Data Warehouses, CRM with Websites, CRM with GP and QuickBooks, other products with Dynamics GP including GP Manufacturing, SharePoint with ERP packages, and various additional web service and application integration's. 
Software Design and Development: New software solutions that are unique to our customer’s businesses. Our solutions include custom Websites and Business Applications that automate business processes to increase sales and decrease costs.
Training: Provides practical training on business software such as CRM, SharePoint, Lync, Word, Excel, Outlook and PowerPoint. We also provide technical training and mentoring on system administration, configuration and development for our platform including CRM, SharePoint, SQL and related technologies.

items.name: Hanebutt Technologies, Inc.
items.description:
Hanebutt Technologies used to be just another of the typical IT support companies out there. Once, we were just about reactions to IT problems for our clients, showing up to fix computers when they were broken, selling some new products when the old ones just wouldn’t turn back on again. It was just the way of things.

No more, though. Seven years ago, we changed our ownership and leadership, and that meant renewing the way we work with our clients. We want to be more than just the fix-it people now – we want to be your partner. You use your information technology every day, but so many businesses just see it as a boring old tool to get the job done.

We think IT can be more than that.

Today, we focus on the needs of your business before the needs of your technology. The two should go hand-in-hand. When we come to work with you, our first questions aren’t going to be about your computer systems. We want to know who you are and what you want your technology to do for you.

items.name: Aureon
items.description: Aureon Technology is a full-service technology provider established in 1994 to provide businesses with solutions for software development and licensing, networking, IT staffing and IT management. By providing a broad range of services, we can offer a suite of solutions that is unrivaled in the region. Technologies that in the past were disparate and fragmented have become interdependent. Web sites rely on databases. Applications rely on wide area networks. And so on. Most technology firms address individual portions of the technology landscape, often creating gaps between areas that need to be tightly knit together. By offering a single-source provider, a company can reduce the complexities associated with coordinating services between multiple providers.
